-- Egypt’s Islamists Won’t Harm Tourism, Eisa Tells Handelsblatt
-- B y   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 2012-01-04T08:03:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/egypt-s-islamists-won-t-harm-tourism-eisa-tells-handelsblatt.html
Egyptian Trade and Industry Minister
Mahmoud Eisa said victory by Islamist parties in the country’s
elections won’t damage the  tourism industry ,  Handelsblatt 
reported, citing an interview.  Eisa also said  Egypt  is considering asking for aid from the
 International Monetary Fund  as “an option,” and will shortly
begin a series of “road shows” abroad to attract foreign
investment, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Black in Frankfurt at 
 jblack25@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
